# lazybones — agent CLI credentials + run secrets (TEMPLATE).
#
# Copy to `.env` (`make secrets-init`) and fill in the keys for whichever agent
# tools you run. `.env` is gitignored — never commit real keys. The hcom loop and
# the agents it spawns inherit this environment, so a key set here reaches the
# agent CLI the task uses (config `agent_tool`, default `claude`).
#
# You only need the keys for the tools you actually use. `make agents-check`
# shows which CLIs are installed and which keys are set.

# --- Claude Code (Anthropic) — `agent_tool: claude` -------------------------
# Get a key: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# Claude Code also accepts an interactive login (`claude login`) instead of a key.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Codex (OpenAI) — `agent_tool: codex` -----------------------------------
# Get a key: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Codex also accepts `codex login` (ChatGPT auth) instead of a raw key.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- Gemini (Google) — `agent_tool: gemini` ---------------------------------
# Get a key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# --- OpenCode — `agent_tool: opencode` --------------------------------------
# OpenCode is provider-agnostic; it reads whichever of the above keys its
# configured model needs. Set the relevant key above. Optional explicit key:
# OPENCODE_API_KEY=

# --- lazybones daemon secrets (override the committed defaults) --------------
# The bearer token the trusted loop authenticates with (config `loop_token`).
# Override the insecure default for any non-local run.
LAZYBONES_LOOP_TOKEN=lazybones-loop
